1
00:00:13,250 --> 00:00:15,250
[rain pattering]

2
00:00:21,541 --> 00:00:23,541
[eerie score playing]

3
00:00:34,250 --> 00:00:35,250
[thunder crashing]

4
00:00:46,125 --> 00:00:48,999
- [line ringing]
- [man on phone] <i>Hello, hello, hello?</i>

5
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:51,082
Oh, is that the police?

6
00:00:51,083 --> 00:00:54,749
We've got someone here
you might be interested in.

7
00:00:54,750 --> 00:00:56,000
[chuckles softly]

8
00:00:56,958 --> 00:00:59,625
I think we just foiled a robbery.

9
00:01:01,958 --> 00:01:04,040
[siren wailing]

10
00:01:04,041 --> 00:01:06,125
[reporters clamouring]

11
00:01:16,208 --> 00:01:17,208
[gate clangs shut]

12
00:01:23,500 --> 00:01:24,666
[neck cracks]

13
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:29,249
{\an8}- [camera clicks]
- [judge] <i>Feathers McGraw,</i>

14
00:01:29,250 --> 00:01:31,415
{\an8}<i>you have been found guilty</i>

15
00:01:31,416 --> 00:01:34,790
<i>of the attempted robbery
of the Blue Diamond.</i>

16
00:01:34,791 --> 00:01:38,832
<i>If not for the actions
of two upstanding citizens,</i>

17
00:01:38,833 --> 00:01:41,875
<i>you would have succeeded
in your wicked plan.</i>

18
00:01:42,458 --> 00:01:46,207
<i>Therefore, it is the decision
of this court</i>

19
00:01:46,208 --> 00:01:48,707
<i>that for the rest of your natural life,</i>

20
00:01:48,708 --> 00:01:53,666
<i>you'll be removed
to a high-security institution.</i>

21
00:01:55,791 --> 00:01:56,791
{\an8}[children laughing]

22
00:02:02,125 --> 00:02:05,207
[female guard chuckles]
There's no escape from here,

23
00:02:05,208 --> 00:02:07,666
so don't even think about it.

24
00:02:08,166 --> 00:02:09,291
[both gasp]

25
00:02:12,416 --> 00:02:14,416
[ominous score playing]

26
00:02:39,541 --> 00:02:41,541
{\an8}[whimsical score playing]

27
00:03:06,916 --> 00:03:07,874
[score ends]

28
00:03:07,875 --> 00:03:08,958
[alarm ringing]

29
00:03:10,541 --> 00:03:11,541
[ringing stops]

30
00:03:13,875 --> 00:03:14,875
[machine suctioning]

31
00:03:18,625 --> 00:03:19,833
[beeping]

32
00:03:30,666 --> 00:03:32,208
[device buzzing]

33
00:03:33,250 --> 00:03:34,957
[Wallace, over intercom]
<i>Get me up, Gromit.</i>

34
00:03:34,958 --> 00:03:38,916
Another great day of inventing
beckons! [chuckles]

35
00:03:41,666 --> 00:03:44,166
{\an8}[laughing] Oh, top dog!

36
00:03:49,916 --> 00:03:52,041
{\an8}Here we go!

37
00:03:54,625 --> 00:03:56,415
{\an8}Away!

38
00:03:56,416 --> 00:03:57,416
{\an8}Oh!

39
00:03:59,458 --> 00:04:01,083
{\an8}Oh! Lovely.

40
00:04:02,875 --> 00:04:04,041
{\an8}[machine suctioning]

41
00:04:10,625 --> 00:04:12,791
{\an8}[giggles] Ooh! Tickles! [whoops]

42
00:04:14,958 --> 00:04:16,541
{\an8}Whoa!

43
00:04:18,250 --> 00:04:20,291
{\an8}[whooping]

44
00:04:21,041 --> 00:04:22,833
{\an8}Whee!

45
00:04:26,500 --> 00:04:27,333
{\an8}[whooping]

46
00:04:29,208 --> 00:04:30,208
{\an8}[chuckles]

47
00:04:31,875 --> 00:04:33,250
{\an8}Huh? [grunts]

48
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:36,000
{\an8}Oh!

49
00:04:37,666 --> 00:04:38,540
{\an8}Ah.

50
00:04:38,541 --> 00:04:39,833
{\an8}<i>Hit it, Gromit.</i>

51
00:04:43,916 --> 00:04:45,416
- [exclaims]
- [dings]

52
00:04:48,791 --> 00:04:49,875
{\an8}Morning, Gromit.

53
00:04:50,500 --> 00:04:51,332
{\an8}Oh!

54
00:04:51,333 --> 00:04:54,000
How's my favourite pooch, hmm?

55
00:04:56,333 --> 00:04:58,333
Oh, you do look after me, lad.

56
00:05:00,708 --> 00:05:01,832
Very interesting.

57
00:05:01,833 --> 00:05:03,625
- Oh, I must say...
- [toaster ticking]

58
00:05:04,208 --> 00:05:05,916
Mmm. Oh, yes.

59
00:05:12,458 --> 00:05:13,750
{\an8}Mmm. Mmm.

60
00:05:16,541 --> 00:05:17,541
Hmm.

61
00:05:20,500 --> 00:05:23,541
Mmm. Cracking toast, Gromit.

62
00:05:27,708 --> 00:05:29,708
[Wallace munching]

63
00:05:32,458 --> 00:05:34,958
Oh, dear. More bills?

64
00:05:35,833 --> 00:05:38,458
Inventing doesn't come cheap,
does it? [chuckles]

65
00:05:41,166 --> 00:05:43,833
Maybe I'm just making too many gadgets.

66
00:05:46,250 --> 00:05:47,291
[sighs]

67
00:05:49,125 --> 00:05:52,875
Oh, don't worry, lad,
we'll think of something.

68
00:05:54,750 --> 00:05:57,083
You look like you need a good pat.

69
00:05:57,666 --> 00:05:58,958
Come here.

70
00:06:03,083 --> 00:06:04,290
That's it, lad.

71
00:06:04,291 --> 00:06:07,333
My new Pat-O-Matic will oblige.

72
00:06:11,791 --> 00:06:13,624
And if you think that's progress,

73
00:06:13,625 --> 00:06:16,625
wait till you see the next thing
I'm working on. Hmm.

74
00:06:20,125 --> 00:06:21,625
Ooh!

75
00:06:27,375 --> 00:06:28,500
[giggles eagerly]

76
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:31,000
[birds chirping]

77
00:06:38,125 --> 00:06:39,125
[breathes deeply]

78
00:06:50,583 --> 00:06:51,583
[breathes deeply]

79
00:06:53,208 --> 00:06:54,208
[wheels squeaking]

80
00:06:55,833 --> 00:06:57,415
[Wallace] Oh, look out, lad.

81
00:06:57,416 --> 00:06:58,708
Coming through.

82
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:01,207
Phew. [chuckles]

83
00:07:01,208 --> 00:07:04,040
Oh, don't think I haven't noticed, Gromit.

84
00:07:04,041 --> 00:07:07,083
You spend ages
toiling away in this garden.

85
00:07:07,791 --> 00:07:09,708
Well, no more.

86
00:07:11,166 --> 00:07:13,458
- [thudding]
- [ominous score playing]

87
00:07:21,500 --> 00:07:22,833
Hey-hey!

88
00:07:25,208 --> 00:07:27,624
[Wallace] This is my latest invention.

89
00:07:27,625 --> 00:07:29,375
A smart gnome.

90
00:07:29,958 --> 00:07:33,374
Hi, I'm your Nifty Odd-jobbing Robot.

91
00:07:33,375 --> 00:07:34,999
Call me Norbot.

92
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:37,165
[Wallace] Norbot, meet Gromit.

93
00:07:37,166 --> 00:07:39,250
Pleased to meet you, Master Gromit.

94
00:07:40,250 --> 00:07:41,750
[Wallace] He's very friendly.

95
00:07:44,041 --> 00:07:46,457
Whoa, steady on, Norbot. [chuckles]

96
00:07:46,458 --> 00:07:48,041
Well, go on, Chuck.

97
00:07:48,750 --> 00:07:51,374
Why don't you put him
through his little paces?

98
00:07:51,375 --> 00:07:53,458
He is voice-activated.

99
00:07:54,625 --> 00:07:56,624
[chuckles] A bit shy, are we?

100
00:07:56,625 --> 00:07:57,540
All right.

101
00:07:57,541 --> 00:08:01,207
Norbot, make Gromit's garden
neat and tidy.

102
00:08:01,208 --> 00:08:03,125
Neat and tidy.

103
00:08:04,583 --> 00:08:06,790
- Yes, Mr Wallace.
- [beeping]

104
00:08:06,791 --> 00:08:09,582
[Wallace] I pre-programmed him
for you, lad.

105
00:08:09,583 --> 00:08:13,790
He's watched every episode
of <i>DIY Garden Squad</i> there is.

106
00:08:13,791 --> 00:08:17,833
[Norbot] Only two hours to go,
and they still haven't got the patio down!

107
00:08:18,500 --> 00:08:22,458
[Wallace] Just watch him do
all those tedious gardening tasks.

108
00:08:24,458 --> 00:08:26,000
Chop, chop, chop!

109
00:08:29,166 --> 00:08:30,082
Mowing!

110
00:08:30,083 --> 00:08:33,208
- [chuckles]
- Hey! More mowing!

111
00:08:33,791 --> 00:08:36,000
[Wallace laughs] Don't forget the edges.

112
00:08:36,791 --> 00:08:37,791
Strimmer!

113
00:08:38,875 --> 00:08:40,125
[Wallace] Careful, lad.

114
00:08:40,625 --> 00:08:42,625
[leaf blower whirring]

115
00:08:44,833 --> 00:08:46,958
[Norbot] Pointlessly
blowing leaves around!

116
00:08:47,750 --> 00:08:49,375
[Wallace] Oh! Whoops-a-daisy!

117
00:08:51,708 --> 00:08:53,250
Hedge trim!

118
00:08:53,833 --> 00:08:55,000
Last bit of mowing.

119
00:09:00,916 --> 00:09:03,207
<i>♪ I'm a happy, nifty Norbot ♪</i>

120
00:09:03,208 --> 00:09:05,166
<i>♪ I love to do a job ♪</i>

121
00:09:08,833 --> 00:09:10,499
Neat and tidy!

122
00:09:10,500 --> 00:09:12,999
[people exclaiming, applauding]

123
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:14,165
[Wallace chuckles]

124
00:09:14,166 --> 00:09:16,249
Oh, he's a little treasure, that one!

125
00:09:16,250 --> 00:09:18,082
Amazing job!

126
00:09:18,083 --> 00:09:20,332
And very convenient.

127
00:09:20,333 --> 00:09:24,790
Well, well, looks like
you've made the cut, Norbot.

128
00:09:24,791 --> 00:09:27,040
Better take a bow, hmm?

129
00:09:27,041 --> 00:09:28,749
[Norbot] Bowing! Bowing again!

130
00:09:28,750 --> 00:09:30,915
- Where did you get him from?
- [Norbot] Thank you.

131
00:09:30,916 --> 00:09:33,832
Well, actually, I made him myself.

132
00:09:33,833 --> 00:09:36,332
What fun! Is he for hire?

133
00:09:36,333 --> 00:09:38,458
Is he for hire? [chuckles nervously]

134
00:09:39,541 --> 00:09:40,666
Oh!

135
00:09:44,541 --> 00:09:46,291
Come on. I need your help.

136
00:09:49,375 --> 00:09:51,540
Not you, lad. Norbot.

137
00:09:51,541 --> 00:09:53,041
Yes, Mr Wallace.

138
00:09:53,541 --> 00:09:55,041
How may I assist?

139
00:09:55,708 --> 00:09:59,124
Come along, Norbot, lad.
We've got work to do.

140
00:09:59,125 --> 00:10:00,708
[Norbot] Righto, Mr Wallace.

141
00:10:03,250 --> 00:10:06,082
[Mackintosh] It's a crime.
That's what it is, a crime.

142
00:10:06,083 --> 00:10:09,041
That you and I can't be together.

143
00:10:10,416 --> 00:10:12,416
Not yet, my sweetness.

144
00:10:12,916 --> 00:10:13,999
{\an8}Soon, though.

145
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:15,291
{\an8}- [knock at door]
- Oh! Eh?

146
00:10:16,625 --> 00:10:18,207
- Got a mo, Chief?
- Huh?

147
00:10:18,208 --> 00:10:21,541
I've just finished my investigation
into that missing bike saddle.

148
00:10:22,250 --> 00:10:25,290
I've got witness interviews,
crime scene reports, full forensics.

149
00:10:25,291 --> 00:10:26,207
Mukherjee.

150
00:10:26,208 --> 00:10:28,832
And I checked
the National Bike Saddle database.

151
00:10:28,833 --> 00:10:30,832
- There isn't one, apparently.
- Mukherjee!

152
00:10:30,833 --> 00:10:32,040
Chief?

153
00:10:32,041 --> 00:10:35,082
[sighs wearily]
How long have you been with us now?

154
00:10:35,083 --> 00:10:37,374
Since 9:00 a.m. this morning, Chief.

155
00:10:37,375 --> 00:10:40,874
Well, you can forget
what you've learned at training college.

156
00:10:40,875 --> 00:10:42,457
Because at the end of the day,

157
00:10:42,458 --> 00:10:45,124
there's just one thing
that matters in this job.

158
00:10:45,125 --> 00:10:46,207
A copper's guts.

159
00:10:46,208 --> 00:10:48,625
- Copper's guts, sir?
- Instinct.

160
00:10:50,166 --> 00:10:52,000
The important stuff's not up here.

161
00:10:52,500 --> 00:10:53,915
It's down here.

162
00:10:53,916 --> 00:10:56,957
Yeah, I've got
quite a copper's gut meself, actually.

163
00:10:56,958 --> 00:10:58,750
Oh, I can see that, Chief.

164
00:10:59,333 --> 00:11:01,332
I mean, er... [chuckles nervously]

165
00:11:01,333 --> 00:11:04,458
I didn't mean I can see... it.

166
00:11:05,458 --> 00:11:07,082
Oh, is that Feathers McGraw?

167
00:11:07,083 --> 00:11:08,458
[gasps] What? Where?

168
00:11:09,875 --> 00:11:11,458
Oh. [chuckles] That.

169
00:11:11,958 --> 00:11:14,666
Well, there you go, a copper's gut.

170
00:11:15,250 --> 00:11:17,040
He stole the Blue Diamond, right?

171
00:11:17,041 --> 00:11:18,124
Oh, he tried,

172
00:11:18,125 --> 00:11:20,916
but he couldn't escape
the long arm of the law.

173
00:11:21,833 --> 00:11:24,332
- [patriotic score playing]
<i>- Oh, yes, I played my part.</i>

174
00:11:24,333 --> 00:11:25,416
[telephone ringing]

175
00:11:27,916 --> 00:11:29,124
Hello, hello, hello?

176
00:11:29,125 --> 00:11:31,165
[Wallace on phone] <i>Oh, is that the police?</i>

177
00:11:31,166 --> 00:11:34,458
[Mackintosh] <i>The Blue Diamond
ended up back in the museum vault.</i>

178
00:11:35,541 --> 00:11:37,291
<i>I locked it up meself,</i>

179
00:11:37,875 --> 00:11:39,375
<i>well out of harm's way.</i>

180
00:11:40,625 --> 00:11:43,249
Oh, I'd love to crack a case like that.

181
00:11:43,250 --> 00:11:44,999
You must be dead proud, Chief.

182
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:47,290
It's not... It's not about pride, Mukherjee.

183
00:11:47,291 --> 00:11:48,999
It's about duty.

184
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:53,290
Which is why I've accepted one last task
before I hang up my truncheon.

185
00:11:53,291 --> 00:11:54,582
Oh?

186
00:11:54,583 --> 00:11:57,124
The new Blue Diamond Exhibition.

187
00:11:57,125 --> 00:11:59,124
The diamond's going back on display?

188
00:11:59,125 --> 00:12:03,415
Oh, aye. I've designed
all the security arrangements meself.

189
00:12:03,416 --> 00:12:04,540
Foolproof.

190
00:12:04,541 --> 00:12:05,749
Yeah.

191
00:12:05,750 --> 00:12:09,082
Well, not unless
Feathers cuts a hole in that skylight.

192
00:12:09,083 --> 00:12:10,165
Skylight?

193
00:12:10,166 --> 00:12:11,957
Or removes the back plate off the air-con.

194
00:12:11,958 --> 00:12:13,582
- Air-what?
- Oh! Actually,

195
00:12:13,583 --> 00:12:15,374
he could just get in
through the gift shop.

196
00:12:15,375 --> 00:12:16,582
There's a gift shop?

197
00:12:16,583 --> 00:12:19,415
Look! Feathers isn't gonna get in, is he?

198
00:12:19,416 --> 00:12:21,625
<i>He's safely banged up in the zoo,</i>

199
00:12:22,208 --> 00:12:24,165
<i>literally doing bird.</i>

200
00:12:24,166 --> 00:12:27,082
Now, I've got a grand opening
to prepare for.

201
00:12:27,083 --> 00:12:29,666
So get out there on the beat,
burn some shoe leather.

202
00:12:30,250 --> 00:12:31,332
Yes!

203
00:12:31,333 --> 00:12:33,665
[clears throat] I mean, yes, sir.

204
00:12:33,666 --> 00:12:34,750
[grunts]

205
00:12:36,333 --> 00:12:41,458
[Wallace] Oh, yes, that's it, Norbot.
Make the letters nice and big.

206
00:12:42,250 --> 00:12:44,457
Oh. [chuckles] That's just smashing.

207
00:12:44,458 --> 00:12:45,583
[chuckles] Ooh.

208
00:12:46,166 --> 00:12:48,291
I think you're going to like this, Gromit.

209
00:12:48,958 --> 00:12:49,875
Da-na!

210
00:12:50,458 --> 00:12:51,874
Da-na!

211
00:12:51,875 --> 00:12:53,833
[Wallace] Gnome Improvements.

212
00:12:54,583 --> 00:12:57,500
A gnome-based
garden and maintenance service.

213
00:12:58,291 --> 00:13:02,208
I told you we'd find a way
to pay the bills, lad. [chuckles]

214
00:13:05,416 --> 00:13:06,416
Er, Norbot,

215
00:13:07,000 --> 00:13:08,332
{\an8}haven't you missed something?

216
00:13:08,333 --> 00:13:10,958
- Oh. Yes, Mr Wallace.
- [whirring]

217
00:13:16,291 --> 00:13:18,207
Oh, yes. Very good.

218
00:13:18,208 --> 00:13:19,999
Oh, good job, Norbot.

219
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:21,832
[chuckling] Oh, yes.

220
00:13:21,833 --> 00:13:23,665
- [horn honks]
- [woman] Yoo-hoo!

221
00:13:23,666 --> 00:13:26,833
[Wallace] Hmm? Oh! It's Up North News.

222
00:13:27,416 --> 00:13:29,540
Maybe they've heard about our Norbot.

223
00:13:29,541 --> 00:13:32,416
Oh, this'll be great for publicity.

224
00:13:33,083 --> 00:13:37,333
[announcer on TV] <i>And now,
Up North News, presented by Anton Deck.</i>

225
00:13:40,666 --> 00:13:41,665
{\an8}<i>Good evening.</i>

226
00:13:41,666 --> 00:13:44,915
{\an8}<i>Now, we've all heard
of cutting-edge technology.</i>

227
00:13:44,916 --> 00:13:48,249
<i>But how about "cutting hedge" technology?</i>

228
00:13:48,250 --> 00:13:51,500
[chuckles] <i>Onya Doorstep has more.</i>

229
00:13:52,291 --> 00:13:56,500
{\an8}<i>Meet Norbot,
the latest thing in "gnome help."</i>

230
00:13:57,208 --> 00:14:01,457
<i>He's the brainchild
of a smart-thinking local inventor.</i>

231
00:14:01,458 --> 00:14:03,540
Oh. "Smart-thinking."

232
00:14:03,541 --> 00:14:05,500
Oh, thank you very much.

233
00:14:07,333 --> 00:14:11,249
[Onya] <i>So, Wallace,
what can Norbot do around the house?</i>

234
00:14:11,250 --> 00:14:15,457
<i>Oh, well, pretty much everything,
Ms Doorstep.</i>

235
00:14:15,458 --> 00:14:17,750
<i>No job is too small.</i>

236
00:14:18,833 --> 00:14:20,832
<i>♪ I'm a happy, nifty Norbot ♪</i>

237
00:14:20,833 --> 00:14:22,750
<i>♪ I like to trim the hedge ♪</i>

238
00:14:23,416 --> 00:14:24,665
<i>Da-na!</i>

239
00:14:24,666 --> 00:14:25,749
<i>Artistic!</i>

240
00:14:25,750 --> 00:14:29,457
<i>I've been testing him out
here in my own garden,</i>

241
00:14:29,458 --> 00:14:33,083
<i>and he's done a cracking job,
as you can see.</i>

242
00:14:33,750 --> 00:14:37,666
<i>He certainly seems very "user-friendly,"
to use the jargon.</i>

243
00:14:39,458 --> 00:14:43,624
<i>So what inspired you
to create this handy device, Mr Wallace?</i>

244
00:14:43,625 --> 00:14:46,207
[Wallace] <i>Oh, I've always loved inventing,</i>

245
00:14:46,208 --> 00:14:48,415
<i>making things that help people,</i>

246
00:14:48,416 --> 00:14:50,750
<i>and Norbot is so very helpful.</i>

247
00:14:51,791 --> 00:14:55,125
<i>I'd say he's my greatest invention so far.</i>

248
00:14:55,708 --> 00:14:57,290
<i>We charge him up every night,</i>

249
00:14:57,291 --> 00:15:00,832
<i>and the next day, he's raring to go again.</i>

250
00:15:00,833 --> 00:15:03,290
[Onya] <i>He seems very obliging.</i>

251
00:15:03,291 --> 00:15:06,708
[Wallace] <i>Oh, whatever your problem,
he's the answer.</i>

252
00:15:09,833 --> 00:15:12,457
[Onya] <i>Well, sounds like this little gnome</i>

253
00:15:12,458 --> 00:15:15,375
<i>is going to make
a huge difference around here.</i>

254
00:15:16,333 --> 00:15:19,749
<i>This is Onya Doorstep for Up North News.</i>

255
00:15:19,750 --> 00:15:21,833
[foreboding score playing]

256
00:15:22,416 --> 00:15:24,041
[female guard] Cage inspection!

257
00:15:26,458 --> 00:15:27,458
{\an8}[cell door opens]

258
00:15:34,333 --> 00:15:36,291
Move aside, jailbird.

259
00:15:40,833 --> 00:15:41,916
All clear.

260
00:15:42,958 --> 00:15:44,957
What a deadbeat. [chuckles, snorts]

261
00:15:44,958 --> 00:15:47,416
Don't know why everybody thinks
he's so clever.

262
00:15:54,208 --> 00:15:55,416
[Wallace] AI, lad.

263
00:15:56,041 --> 00:16:00,040
See how embracing technology
makes our life better?

264
00:16:00,041 --> 00:16:04,124
[slurps, exhales]
I mean, thanks to that handy device,

265
00:16:04,125 --> 00:16:06,708
we haven't had to use
the old teapot for years.

266
00:16:08,208 --> 00:16:11,791
[chuckles] Oh, yes.
Tech, that's the thing.

267
00:16:12,375 --> 00:16:14,708
So long as it knows who's boss, of course.

268
00:16:16,208 --> 00:16:18,291
[chuckles] Look at him go.

269
00:16:21,708 --> 00:16:22,915
[Norbot] Da-na!

270
00:16:22,916 --> 00:16:25,790
[exclaims] A Wallace Onesie!

271
00:16:25,791 --> 00:16:28,665
Oh! That's champion, that is, Norbot.

272
00:16:28,666 --> 00:16:29,666
[chuckles]

273
00:16:30,208 --> 00:16:31,958
[Norbot] A Wallace Onesie!

274
00:16:32,500 --> 00:16:35,874
[Wallace chuckles]
Oh, I think this will fit perfectly.

275
00:16:35,875 --> 00:16:37,166
[Norbot] Perfectly.

276
00:16:41,125 --> 00:16:44,125
[Eric Coates's "By the Sleepy Lagoon"
playing on radio]

277
00:16:49,750 --> 00:16:50,832
{\an8}[door opens]

278
00:16:50,833 --> 00:16:52,415
[door creaking]

279
00:16:52,416 --> 00:16:55,124
- [Norbot humming happily]
- [door closes]

280
00:16:55,125 --> 00:16:57,333
Evening, Master Gromit.

281
00:17:01,500 --> 00:17:02,500
{\an8}[music stops]

282
00:17:13,166 --> 00:17:15,083
Norbot recharge time.

283
00:17:15,833 --> 00:17:17,833
[moaning, shuddering]

284
00:17:19,916 --> 00:17:20,916
[Norbot gurgling]

285
00:17:27,541 --> 00:17:28,541
[gurgling faster]

286
00:17:43,125 --> 00:17:44,125
[Gromit sighs]

287
00:17:46,125 --> 00:17:48,125
[light humming]

288
00:17:51,833 --> 00:17:52,833
[gurgling stops]

289
00:17:57,166 --> 00:17:58,166
[Gromit sighs]

290
00:17:59,041 --> 00:18:01,041
[gurgling and humming resume]

291
00:18:04,291 --> 00:18:07,124
Recharge nearly 1%.

292
00:18:07,125 --> 00:18:09,208
[gurgling and humming resume]

293
00:18:28,541 --> 00:18:30,957
Recharge time reactivated.

294
00:18:30,958 --> 00:18:32,958
[gurgling]

295
00:18:40,541 --> 00:18:42,625
Recharge nearly 2%.

296
00:18:46,250 --> 00:18:47,375
[owl hoots]

297
00:18:48,166 --> 00:18:50,166
[gurgling continues]

298
00:18:57,666 --> 00:18:59,666
[foreboding score playing]

299
00:19:03,583 --> 00:19:05,583
[thunder rumbling]

300
00:19:36,208 --> 00:19:38,208
[thunder rumbling]

301
00:19:59,916 --> 00:20:01,916
[guard snoring]

302
00:20:29,291 --> 00:20:30,500
[beeping]

303
00:20:34,500 --> 00:20:35,582
[sniffs]

304
00:20:35,583 --> 00:20:36,875
[inhaling]

305
00:20:39,916 --> 00:20:40,750
[sneeze stops]

306
00:20:43,250 --> 00:20:44,250
[exhales]

307
00:20:47,250 --> 00:20:48,665
[inhaling]

308
00:20:48,666 --> 00:20:49,750
[muffled sneeze]

309
00:20:54,791 --> 00:20:55,875
[exhales]

310
00:20:56,750 --> 00:20:58,750
[continues snoring]

311
00:21:04,791 --> 00:21:06,708
[error tone buzzing]

312
00:22:03,375 --> 00:22:06,416
- [videogame music plays]
- [Wallace] <i>Welcome to my Top Secret Files.</i>

313
00:22:09,333 --> 00:22:11,333
{\an8}[ominous score playing]

314
00:22:32,125 --> 00:22:33,916
- [neck cracks]
- [thunder rumbles]

315
00:23:08,708 --> 00:23:10,708
[warbling]

316
00:23:14,875 --> 00:23:15,875
[warbling stops]

317
00:23:19,583 --> 00:23:21,416
[thunder crashing]

318
00:23:22,500 --> 00:23:24,625
[Norbot] New instructions received.

319
00:23:30,500 --> 00:23:32,375
No job is too small.

320
00:23:33,791 --> 00:23:35,916
- [tools whirring]
- [thunder crashing]

321
00:23:46,875 --> 00:23:48,875
[tools whirring, clanking]

322
00:23:55,041 --> 00:23:56,041
[thunder rumbling]

323
00:24:07,458 --> 00:24:08,875
[thunder crashing]

324
00:24:11,708 --> 00:24:13,457
[alarm rings, stops]

325
00:24:13,458 --> 00:24:15,541
[machinery whirring, rattling]

326
00:24:29,666 --> 00:24:31,540
- [Wallace] <i>Get me up, Gromit.</i>
- [device buzzing]

327
00:24:31,541 --> 00:24:33,958
<i>We've got a right busy day ahead.</i>

328
00:24:38,333 --> 00:24:39,874
- [machinery thudding]
- Thanks, lad.

329
00:24:39,875 --> 00:24:41,083
<i>Whee!</i>

330
00:24:41,750 --> 00:24:43,875
- [door creaks open]
- [mechanical footsteps]

331
00:24:55,583 --> 00:24:57,083
[ominous sting plays]

332
00:25:07,916 --> 00:25:09,125
- [door opens]
- [Wallace grunts]

333
00:25:10,500 --> 00:25:11,500
Oh-ho!

334
00:25:12,250 --> 00:25:13,500
Morning, team.

335
00:25:14,333 --> 00:25:15,333
Mmm.

336
00:25:15,833 --> 00:25:18,165
Oh! Loads of new messages.

337
00:25:18,166 --> 00:25:19,290
[beeps]

338
00:25:19,291 --> 00:25:22,124
[woman 1] <i>Gnome Improvements?
I saw you on the telly.</i>

339
00:25:22,125 --> 00:25:23,749
<i>Could Norbot come and mow my...</i>

340
00:25:23,750 --> 00:25:25,040
[man 1] <i>...new lily pond...</i>

341
00:25:25,041 --> 00:25:26,457
[woman 2] <i>...with a stump-grinder...</i>

342
00:25:26,458 --> 00:25:28,415
[man 2] <i>...and put well-rotted manure...</i>

343
00:25:28,416 --> 00:25:30,208
[woman 3] <i>...inside my conservatory...</i>

344
00:25:31,041 --> 00:25:32,999
Talk about celebrity, lad.

345
00:25:33,000 --> 00:25:35,750
He's a "household gnome." [chuckles]

346
00:25:36,583 --> 00:25:40,416
At this rate, we'll need
a whole army of Norbots. [chuckles]

347
00:25:41,416 --> 00:25:42,582
[claps]

348
00:25:42,583 --> 00:25:45,000
[loud rhythmic thudding]

349
00:25:45,833 --> 00:25:46,916
Hmm?

350
00:25:47,458 --> 00:25:48,415
Eh?

351
00:25:48,416 --> 00:25:50,500
- [thudding continues]
- [objects rattling]

352
00:26:07,291 --> 00:26:09,375
[thudding draws closer]

353
00:26:14,000 --> 00:26:16,000
[dramatic score playing]

354
00:26:26,708 --> 00:26:28,333
What on earth...

355
00:26:28,833 --> 00:26:29,832
Hmm?

356
00:26:29,833 --> 00:26:32,916
More Norbots for Mr Wallace.

357
00:26:33,500 --> 00:26:35,332
Er... Eh...

358
00:26:35,333 --> 00:26:36,583
[chuckles nervously]

359
00:26:42,500 --> 00:26:45,208
Well, that <i>is</i> smart.

360
00:26:46,125 --> 00:26:50,249
It's like he knows what we need
before we even know ourselves.

361
00:26:50,250 --> 00:26:52,875
Ha! The more gnomes, the merrier.

362
00:26:53,416 --> 00:26:54,666
Right, Gromit?

363
00:26:55,250 --> 00:26:57,040
The more gnomes, the merrier.

364
00:26:57,041 --> 00:26:58,749
[Evil Norbots] Yes, Mr Wallace!

365
00:26:58,750 --> 00:27:01,957
[Wallace chuckles]
What could possibly go wrong?

366
00:27:01,958 --> 00:27:04,041
[ominous score playing]

367
00:27:06,375 --> 00:27:08,000
[Wallace] That's it. Up you go.

368
00:27:10,708 --> 00:27:11,707
Uh-huh.

369
00:27:11,708 --> 00:27:13,874
A bit of fine-tuning...

370
00:27:13,875 --> 00:27:15,125
Oh, that's good.

371
00:27:16,250 --> 00:27:18,374
No need for us to go with them, Gromit.

372
00:27:18,375 --> 00:27:22,083
I just track them
with my new "gnoming device."

373
00:27:23,708 --> 00:27:25,874
Ah! Lovely tea.

374
00:27:25,875 --> 00:27:31,375
All we have to do is sit back
and let the machines take the strain.

375
00:27:33,000 --> 00:27:34,000
Right, Gromit?

376
00:27:35,291 --> 00:27:36,375
Gromit?

377
00:27:37,666 --> 00:27:40,083
Gromit? Gromit?

378
00:27:41,208 --> 00:27:44,457
[on radio] <i>I said we don't need
to go with them.</i> [chuckles]

379
00:27:44,458 --> 00:27:46,875
<i>Don't you trust my inventions, lad?</i>

380
00:27:55,666 --> 00:27:57,082
<i>I don't know.</i>

381
00:27:57,083 --> 00:27:59,374
Hmm. Never mind.

382
00:27:59,375 --> 00:28:01,875
Time to unleash the gnomes!

383
00:28:04,500 --> 00:28:05,915
Go! Go! Go! Go!

384
00:28:05,916 --> 00:28:08,166
- [whoops]
- [laughs]

385
00:28:09,500 --> 00:28:10,583
[Evil Norbots whooping]

386
00:28:13,708 --> 00:28:15,874
- Yeah!
- Rad!

387
00:28:15,875 --> 00:28:19,374
[Wallace] Oh, yes.
All present and correct. Hmm.

388
00:28:19,375 --> 00:28:21,874
Remember, I want you all working

389
00:28:21,875 --> 00:28:24,165
<i>- like a finely-tuned machine.</i>
- [doorbell rings]

390
00:28:24,166 --> 00:28:26,250
[whimsical music playing]

391
00:28:30,458 --> 00:28:31,291
Ow!

392
00:28:34,583 --> 00:28:38,040
[Evil Norbots]
<i>♪ Oh, we're happy, nifty Norbots ♪</i>

393
00:28:38,041 --> 00:28:40,332
<i>♪ We love to do our job ♪</i>

394
00:28:40,333 --> 00:28:43,040
<i>♪ When we come round and fix your house ♪</i>

395
00:28:43,041 --> 00:28:44,875
<i>♪ We make up quite a mob ♪</i>

396
00:28:45,458 --> 00:28:47,582
<i>♪ We dig and paint, we plant and snip ♪</i>

397
00:28:47,583 --> 00:28:49,874
<i>♪ We'll break our little backs ♪</i>

398
00:28:49,875 --> 00:28:52,374
<i>♪ And never stop to have a brew ♪</i>

399
00:28:52,375 --> 00:28:54,416
<i>♪ 'Cause we got battery packs ♪</i>

400
00:28:54,916 --> 00:28:56,207
This is the police.

401
00:28:56,208 --> 00:28:58,040
Come down quietly.

402
00:28:58,041 --> 00:29:00,249
You're only making this
harder on yourself.

403
00:29:00,250 --> 00:29:01,707
[whimpering]

404
00:29:01,708 --> 00:29:03,457
- [Evil Norbot] Beep, beep!
- [both gasp]

405
00:29:03,458 --> 00:29:04,874
Beep, beep! Coming through!

406
00:29:04,875 --> 00:29:06,125
[both shriek]

407
00:29:06,958 --> 00:29:08,874
[music continues]

408
00:29:08,875 --> 00:29:09,958
[woman moans]

409
00:29:10,958 --> 00:29:12,375
Patio-chop!

410
00:29:13,875 --> 00:29:16,915
<i>♪ Oh, we're jolly, useful Norbots ♪</i>

411
00:29:16,916 --> 00:29:18,541
<i>♪ We do all sorts of stuff ♪</i>

412
00:29:19,125 --> 00:29:21,290
<i>♪ When we get asked to do a task ♪</i>

413
00:29:21,291 --> 00:29:23,707
<i>♪ We can't work hard enough! ♪</i>

414
00:29:23,708 --> 00:29:25,999
<i>♪ We push and pull and saw and chop ♪</i>

415
00:29:26,000 --> 00:29:28,374
<i>♪ We think our chores are fun ♪</i>

416
00:29:28,375 --> 00:29:29,540
<i>♪ We won't delay ♪</i>

417
00:29:29,541 --> 00:29:33,000
<i>♪ Keep out our way until the job is done ♪</i>

418
00:29:34,000 --> 00:29:36,499
The Norbots are a triumph, Gromit.

419
00:29:36,500 --> 00:29:38,832
We'll soon have those bills paid off.

420
00:29:38,833 --> 00:29:41,583
- [music continues]
- [Evil Norbots vocalising along]

421
00:29:44,000 --> 00:29:44,958
[weathervane clangs]

422
00:29:46,000 --> 00:29:48,375
[Evil Norbots whistling along]

423
00:30:00,541 --> 00:30:02,708
- [music ends]
- [Evil Norbot] Neat and tidy.

424
00:30:09,958 --> 00:30:11,958
[Evil Norbots vocalising cheerfully]

425
00:30:18,500 --> 00:30:20,833
- [vocalising stops]
- [foreboding score playing]

426
00:30:34,083 --> 00:30:36,500
Oh, happy birthday, Mavis.

427
00:30:37,083 --> 00:30:38,958
Oh, smashing!

428
00:30:41,041 --> 00:30:43,875
Oh! What's happened to me glass table?

429
00:30:46,875 --> 00:30:47,875
[gasps]

430
00:30:48,583 --> 00:30:49,875
Where's me tools?

431
00:30:51,583 --> 00:30:54,207
[gasps] Where's me shed?

432
00:30:54,208 --> 00:30:56,416
Where's our drainpipe?

433
00:31:23,333 --> 00:31:24,790
- [telephones ringing]
- Hello? Police.

434
00:31:24,791 --> 00:31:27,457
- Another burglary? What's the address?
- [ringing continues]

435
00:31:27,458 --> 00:31:28,915
Hello? Police.

436
00:31:28,916 --> 00:31:31,624
- A weathervane? When did it go missing?
- [ringing continues]

437
00:31:31,625 --> 00:31:32,915
Hello? Police.

438
00:31:32,916 --> 00:31:35,500
[chuckling]
Someone's pinched your big butt?

439
00:31:36,166 --> 00:31:37,999
Oh! Water butt!

440
00:31:38,000 --> 00:31:39,749
[clears throat] I see what you mean.

441
00:31:39,750 --> 00:31:41,666
- [ringing continues]
- Er, hang on.

442
00:31:43,166 --> 00:31:45,999
[clears throat]
Hello. You have reached the Old Bill.

443
00:31:46,000 --> 00:31:47,207
[Mukherjee yelps]

444
00:31:47,208 --> 00:31:50,457
We're experiencing
a high volume of calls at the moment,

445
00:31:50,458 --> 00:31:53,249
so please leave your crime after the beep.

446
00:31:53,250 --> 00:31:54,166
Beep!

447
00:31:55,250 --> 00:31:56,582
What's going on here?

448
00:31:56,583 --> 00:31:57,832
Oh, Chief!

449
00:31:57,833 --> 00:32:01,707
It's a spate of burglaries,
like, a proper crime wave.

450
00:32:01,708 --> 00:32:04,540
I can't be dealing with a crime wave.

451
00:32:04,541 --> 00:32:06,540
I've got enough on me hands as it is.

452
00:32:06,541 --> 00:32:08,457
What do you think? Blue or black?

453
00:32:08,458 --> 00:32:09,582
For the grand opening.

454
00:32:09,583 --> 00:32:10,915
Er...

455
00:32:10,916 --> 00:32:11,958
Blue?

456
00:32:13,916 --> 00:32:16,332
Ah, yeah. See what you're saying.

457
00:32:16,333 --> 00:32:17,624
Matches the diamond.

458
00:32:17,625 --> 00:32:19,707
Anyroad, about these robberies...

459
00:32:19,708 --> 00:32:23,957
I've been building this crime wall,
trying to find common themes and such.

460
00:32:23,958 --> 00:32:26,665
Never... never mind crime walls.

461
00:32:26,666 --> 00:32:28,957
What's your copper's gut telling you?

462
00:32:28,958 --> 00:32:32,290
{\an8}Well, all the clues
seem to point to this man,

463
00:32:32,291 --> 00:32:33,957
{\an8}a local inventor.

464
00:32:33,958 --> 00:32:35,374
Wallace?

465
00:32:35,375 --> 00:32:39,082
The upstanding citizen
who helped put Feathers behind bars?

466
00:32:39,083 --> 00:32:40,374
Yeah. Hey, why not?

467
00:32:40,375 --> 00:32:43,540
You catch one supervillain,
doesn't make you a saint, does it?

468
00:32:43,541 --> 00:32:45,749
Well, should we say he's a suspect, then?

469
00:32:45,750 --> 00:32:47,458
Just bring him in and book him.

470
00:32:47,958 --> 00:32:49,624
I've got a speech to write.

471
00:32:49,625 --> 00:32:50,624
Really?

472
00:32:50,625 --> 00:32:53,166
Don't we need evidence?

473
00:32:53,791 --> 00:32:54,790
Oh, I don't know.

474
00:32:54,791 --> 00:32:57,957
All these fancy ideas you get
from training college.

475
00:32:57,958 --> 00:33:00,333
[resigned sigh] Right. Come on, then.

476
00:33:01,875 --> 00:33:02,875
[news intro plays]

477
00:33:04,708 --> 00:33:05,708
{\an8}[intro ends]

478
00:33:06,416 --> 00:33:07,665
<i>News just in.</i>

479
00:33:07,666 --> 00:33:11,707
<i>We're getting reports of a crime wave
affecting gardens across the region.</i>

480
00:33:11,708 --> 00:33:13,250
<i>Onya Doorstep has more.</i>

481
00:33:14,083 --> 00:33:16,040
[romantic movie score playing on TV]

482
00:33:16,041 --> 00:33:17,499
- [score turns ominous]
<i>- The robots!</i>

483
00:33:17,500 --> 00:33:19,374
<i>They're taking over the world!</i>

484
00:33:19,375 --> 00:33:21,541
<i>They'll destroy us all, I tell you!</i>

485
00:33:25,583 --> 00:33:28,124
Oh. That's a bit hasty, Norbot.

486
00:33:28,125 --> 00:33:29,999
I might have been watching that.

487
00:33:30,000 --> 00:33:32,375
Time to relax, Mr Wallace.

488
00:33:32,958 --> 00:33:35,791
[Wallace] Oh, yes,
I do like a bit of relaxation.

489
00:33:36,958 --> 00:33:38,791
- [warbling]
- Huh?

490
00:33:41,041 --> 00:33:42,291
Eh?

491
00:33:45,250 --> 00:33:47,041
[playing Brahms's "Lullaby"]

492
00:33:47,625 --> 00:33:49,166
Ah... Oh!

493
00:33:52,166 --> 00:33:54,000
Er, what's all this in aid of?

494
00:33:54,666 --> 00:33:56,083
Massage, Mr Wallace?

495
00:33:57,208 --> 00:33:59,624
Oh. Oh, yes. Oh.

496
00:33:59,625 --> 00:34:01,833
Oh, oh, that's lovely.

497
00:34:06,500 --> 00:34:09,458
{\an8}Oh, dear, you are spoiling me.

498
00:34:10,000 --> 00:34:11,083
Snoozy choc?

499
00:34:11,666 --> 00:34:14,083
[chuckles] Oh! Don't mind if I do.

500
00:34:16,041 --> 00:34:18,458
- Come along.
- Oh, steady on.

501
00:34:19,458 --> 00:34:21,290
Drink up, Mr Wallace.

502
00:34:21,291 --> 00:34:22,958
[Wallace moaning contentedly]

503
00:34:25,583 --> 00:34:27,583
[hiccups, snores]

504
00:34:29,833 --> 00:34:31,833
[foreboding score playing]

505
00:34:47,541 --> 00:34:48,583
[tyres screech]

506
00:34:53,916 --> 00:34:55,915
[tools whirring in basement]

507
00:34:55,916 --> 00:34:58,000
[Wallace snoring]

508
00:35:11,625 --> 00:35:13,625
[electricity crackling]

509
00:35:34,333 --> 00:35:36,333
[dramatic score playing]

510
00:36:10,500 --> 00:36:12,874
- [toy squeaks underfoot]
- [whirring stops]

511
00:36:12,875 --> 00:36:14,291
[squeaks softly]

512
00:36:27,916 --> 00:36:29,166
[toy squeaking]

513
00:36:35,375 --> 00:36:36,500
[groggily] Hmm?

514
00:36:37,500 --> 00:36:39,583
[moans, continues snoring]

515
00:36:48,250 --> 00:36:49,416
[Pat-O-Matic whirring]

516
00:36:51,625 --> 00:36:52,625
[grunting]

517
00:36:53,541 --> 00:36:55,540
Hey! What the... What... [sputters]

518
00:36:55,541 --> 00:36:56,666
Gromit? [grunts]

519
00:36:59,750 --> 00:37:00,583
What on earth?

520
00:37:02,166 --> 00:37:04,415
What? Is something wrong?

521
00:37:04,416 --> 00:37:06,041
Is it the Norbots?

522
00:37:06,708 --> 00:37:09,124
Well, this had better be important, lad.

523
00:37:09,125 --> 00:37:11,624
I don't know what's got into you lately.

524
00:37:11,625 --> 00:37:12,583
[huffs]

525
00:37:16,208 --> 00:37:18,790
Well, I'll go to the top of my stairs.

526
00:37:18,791 --> 00:37:21,166
That's absolutely...

527
00:37:21,708 --> 00:37:22,708
spotless!

528
00:37:25,916 --> 00:37:28,250
- [Evil Norbots humming softly]
- Oh! Look at them.

529
00:37:29,041 --> 00:37:30,582
Oh, yes.

530
00:37:30,583 --> 00:37:33,165
Oh, you are good gnomes,

531
00:37:33,166 --> 00:37:36,083
doing all these chores
at this time of night.

532
00:37:36,916 --> 00:37:40,749
I don't know why you were so keen
to show me though, lad.

533
00:37:40,750 --> 00:37:43,249
Couldn't it have waited till the morning?

534
00:37:43,250 --> 00:37:44,832
[Evil Norbot gurgling softly]

535
00:37:44,833 --> 00:37:47,041
[chuckles] Daft pooch.

536
00:37:47,750 --> 00:37:48,749
[yawns]

537
00:37:48,750 --> 00:37:52,708
Well, I've got a nap to finish
before I turn in for the night.

538
00:37:53,916 --> 00:37:57,707
Oh, yes. Norbot, my best invention ever.

539
00:37:57,708 --> 00:37:59,750
[ominous score playing]

540
00:38:02,708 --> 00:38:04,083
- [knock at door]
- Ooh.

541
00:38:04,833 --> 00:38:06,790
Er, did you order a pizza, lad?

542
00:38:06,791 --> 00:38:09,499
- [knocking continues]
- All right, all right. Hold your horses.

543
00:38:09,500 --> 00:38:11,082
- [screaming] Police!
- [gasps]

544
00:38:11,083 --> 00:38:12,541
- [crashes, yelps]
- Ooh!

545
00:38:13,291 --> 00:38:14,541
[muffled] Oops. Sorry.

546
00:38:15,208 --> 00:38:17,332
[sighs] Give me strength.

547
00:38:17,333 --> 00:38:19,290
Right. Let's get this over with.

548
00:38:19,291 --> 00:38:20,874
Get what over with?

549
00:38:20,875 --> 00:38:23,208
We have a warrant to search your premises.

550
00:38:24,083 --> 00:38:26,374
Mukherjee, read him his rights.

551
00:38:26,375 --> 00:38:28,957
[clears throat]
Anything you say may be taken down

552
00:38:28,958 --> 00:38:30,582
and used as evidence against you.

553
00:38:30,583 --> 00:38:32,749
But I haven't done anything.

554
00:38:32,750 --> 00:38:35,665
[Mukherjee] We believe you to be guilty
of theft by gnome.

555
00:38:35,666 --> 00:38:38,165
I'm guilty of theft by gnome?

556
00:38:38,166 --> 00:38:40,957
Ha-ha! There you go. He admits it.

557
00:38:40,958 --> 00:38:42,165
Write that down.

558
00:38:42,166 --> 00:38:43,749
Oh, this is ridiculous.

559
00:38:43,750 --> 00:38:45,665
My Norbots aren't thieves.

560
00:38:45,666 --> 00:38:49,915
They're down in my workshop right now,
doing a bit of spring cleaning.

561
00:38:49,916 --> 00:38:52,457
[gasps] There's our evidence, Chief.

562
00:38:52,458 --> 00:38:55,083
All right. Check them out, then.

563
00:38:57,666 --> 00:38:59,666
[computer beeping softly]

564
00:39:02,541 --> 00:39:05,166
- Well, I don't see any gnomes.
- Eh?

565
00:39:05,791 --> 00:39:09,582
They were here a moment ago.
I don't understand it.

566
00:39:09,583 --> 00:39:13,332
Er, they must have just popped out
to finish a job.

567
00:39:13,333 --> 00:39:16,624
Look, sunshine,
I have not got time for your games.

568
00:39:16,625 --> 00:39:17,708
Eh?

569
00:39:18,583 --> 00:39:20,750
What... Where are you going, Chief?

570
00:39:21,333 --> 00:39:24,250
I'm off to get me tash trimmed,
for the big day.

571
00:39:24,833 --> 00:39:26,040
Anyway, look,

572
00:39:26,041 --> 00:39:29,249
if you need evidence, Mukherjee,
find some.

573
00:39:29,250 --> 00:39:30,832
I don't care what it takes.

574
00:39:30,833 --> 00:39:32,374
Get this man behind bars

575
00:39:32,375 --> 00:39:33,665
- where he belongs.
- [gulps]

576
00:39:33,666 --> 00:39:36,375
I want this case wrapped up, pronto.

577
00:39:37,625 --> 00:39:40,332
- Understood, sir.
- [door slams shut]

578
00:39:40,333 --> 00:39:43,041
Right. Evidence.

579
00:39:44,666 --> 00:39:45,874
Evidence?

580
00:39:45,875 --> 00:39:48,666
This is PC Mukherjee calling for backup.

581
00:39:49,250 --> 00:39:50,708
We'll need a van.

582
00:39:51,458 --> 00:39:54,083
- A big one.
- [Wallace] Huh?

583
00:39:55,625 --> 00:39:56,625
{\an8}[alarm ringing]

584
00:39:59,416 --> 00:40:00,416
[alarm stops]

585
00:40:12,083 --> 00:40:15,332
{\an8}[Wallace, over intercom]
<i>Er, Gromit? Get me up, lad.</i>

586
00:40:15,333 --> 00:40:16,750
<i>There's a good pooch.</i>

587
00:40:18,083 --> 00:40:19,999
Oh! Wait a mo.

588
00:40:20,000 --> 00:40:21,708
You can't, can you?

589
00:40:22,833 --> 00:40:25,500
They've taken all me inventions away.

590
00:40:26,208 --> 00:40:30,207
For forensic examination or something.

591
00:40:30,208 --> 00:40:32,290
[scoffs] Outrageous! [screams]

592
00:40:32,291 --> 00:40:33,541
[muffled thud upstairs]

593
00:40:36,083 --> 00:40:39,166
[Mukherjee] <i>We believe you to be guilty
of theft by gnome.</i>

594
00:40:40,041 --> 00:40:42,208
[Wallace] <i>They were here a moment ago.</i>

595
00:40:42,791 --> 00:40:44,790
[Mackintosh] <i>Well, I don't see any gnomes.</i>

596
00:40:44,791 --> 00:40:46,124
[muffled thudding upstairs]

597
00:40:46,125 --> 00:40:48,874
[panting] Who needs technology anyway?

598
00:40:48,875 --> 00:40:50,207
Ha! Not me.

599
00:40:50,208 --> 00:40:52,291
[gasps, yelps]

600
00:40:52,958 --> 00:40:54,165
Whoa!

601
00:40:54,166 --> 00:40:55,791
[shudders] That's nippy.

602
00:40:56,541 --> 00:40:58,207
[screaming]

603
00:40:58,208 --> 00:41:00,124
Whoa!

604
00:41:00,125 --> 00:41:01,083
[grunts]

605
00:41:01,666 --> 00:41:03,750
[groans] Me begonias.

606
00:41:12,250 --> 00:41:14,875
[Wallace, upstairs]
I think I need a cup of tea, lad.

607
00:41:19,375 --> 00:41:20,457
[glass shatters]

608
00:41:20,458 --> 00:41:22,541
[suspenseful score playing]

609
00:41:31,291 --> 00:41:33,291
[water drips, echoes]

610
00:41:40,208 --> 00:41:42,250
[Wallace groaning]

611
00:41:44,750 --> 00:41:46,375
Oh. Oh, right. Tea.

612
00:41:48,166 --> 00:41:51,749
I suppose we'll just have to make it
the old way. Hmm.

613
00:41:51,750 --> 00:41:53,124
Ouch!

614
00:41:53,125 --> 00:41:54,375
Oh! Oh.

615
00:41:54,958 --> 00:41:56,707
How do you do this now?

616
00:41:56,708 --> 00:42:00,791
I haven't used one of these for so long,
I've forgotten how they work.

617
00:42:01,416 --> 00:42:02,958
[straining]

618
00:42:05,416 --> 00:42:06,708
It's broken!

619
00:42:08,291 --> 00:42:10,665
There's clearly been a mistake.

620
00:42:10,666 --> 00:42:12,875
My Norbots are innocent.

621
00:42:13,458 --> 00:42:15,500
You believe me, don't you, lad?

622
00:42:20,000 --> 00:42:21,000
Don't you, lad?

623
00:42:23,083 --> 00:42:24,499
Oh.

624
00:42:24,500 --> 00:42:27,666
Well, I think you've said
quite enough, Gromit.

625
00:42:28,583 --> 00:42:31,457
You've never trusted my Norbot, have you?

626
00:42:31,458 --> 00:42:33,707
And I made him just for you.

627
00:42:33,708 --> 00:42:37,582
Mark my words, the police will be back
soon enough to apologise.

628
00:42:37,583 --> 00:42:38,665
[knock at door]

629
00:42:38,666 --> 00:42:41,208
Aha! What did I tell you? [chuckles]

630
00:42:41,750 --> 00:42:43,083
There they are now.

631
00:42:44,083 --> 00:42:47,582
Everything will be right as rain
before you can say...

632
00:42:47,583 --> 00:42:50,040
Nasty, crooked, thieving little toerag!

633
00:42:50,041 --> 00:42:51,540
- Huh?
- [angry shouting]

634
00:42:51,541 --> 00:42:54,457
- [man] Where's our stuff?
- I... I want a refund.

635
00:42:54,458 --> 00:42:56,582
What've your gnomes done with me bathtub?

636
00:42:56,583 --> 00:42:58,083
And where's me glasses?

637
00:42:58,625 --> 00:43:01,499
Oh. [chuckles] They're on me head. Sorry!

638
00:43:01,500 --> 00:43:03,874
- [angry shouting continues]
- [woman] Where's my big butt?

639
00:43:03,875 --> 00:43:07,207
I'm live
outside the West Wallaby Street house

640
00:43:07,208 --> 00:43:09,915
of the evil inventor, Mr Wallace.

641
00:43:09,916 --> 00:43:11,124
{\an8}Evil?

642
00:43:11,125 --> 00:43:13,832
{\an8}Er, don't you mean "smart-thinking"?

643
00:43:13,833 --> 00:43:16,665
Oh, you think it's smart
to teach gnomes to steal?

644
00:43:16,666 --> 00:43:18,165
No!

645
00:43:18,166 --> 00:43:22,583
But if only my gnomes were here,
maybe I could clear my name.

646
00:43:23,375 --> 00:43:26,165
[laughs] Well, where <i>are</i> the gnomes?

647
00:43:26,166 --> 00:43:29,082
For the last time, I don't know!

648
00:43:29,083 --> 00:43:31,665
Oh, yeah? Very convenient.

649
00:43:31,666 --> 00:43:33,499
[crowd chanting] Where are the gnomes?

650
00:43:33,500 --> 00:43:35,207
<i>Where are the gnomes?</i>

651
00:43:35,208 --> 00:43:38,499
<i>Where are the gnomes?
Where are the gnomes?</i>

652
00:43:38,500 --> 00:43:41,583
- [chanting continues on TV]
- [ominous score playing]

653
00:43:48,000 --> 00:43:50,333
- [chanting continues]
- [breathing heavily]

654
00:43:51,333 --> 00:43:53,249
This is a nightmare, Gromit.

655
00:43:53,250 --> 00:43:55,665
The police want to throw me in jail,

656
00:43:55,666 --> 00:43:59,166
the neighbours all hate me,
and the press think I'm evil!

657
00:44:00,083 --> 00:44:05,375
And how am I supposed to find my gnomes
if they've taken me gnoming device?

658
00:44:11,333 --> 00:44:12,333
[engine stalling]

659
00:44:18,916 --> 00:44:20,208
[crackles]

660
00:44:27,708 --> 00:44:29,790
[dramatic score playing]

661
00:44:29,791 --> 00:44:30,916
[engine starts]

662
00:44:31,583 --> 00:44:32,583
[engine revving]

663
00:44:38,708 --> 00:44:39,541
What?

664
00:44:40,875 --> 00:44:42,999
Never mind Scotland Yard,

665
00:44:43,000 --> 00:44:45,290
looks more like a scrapyard in here.

666
00:44:45,291 --> 00:44:48,374
It's Wallace's stuff, Chief.
You told me to find some evidence.

667
00:44:48,375 --> 00:44:51,457
I didn't mean
take the whole flippin' house.

668
00:44:51,458 --> 00:44:53,540
I mean, what's this in aid of?

669
00:44:53,541 --> 00:44:54,915
[device whirring, clicking]

670
00:44:54,916 --> 00:44:56,665
Oh! Chief, I wouldn't...

671
00:44:56,666 --> 00:44:57,750
[grunting]

672
00:44:58,708 --> 00:45:00,166
Ow! Get off!

673
00:45:01,250 --> 00:45:04,332
That gizmo
just assaulted a police officer!

674
00:45:04,333 --> 00:45:06,832
Add that to list of charges, Mukherjee.

675
00:45:06,833 --> 00:45:08,415
But that's just it, sir.

676
00:45:08,416 --> 00:45:11,082
There's nothing here
to pin Wallace to the burglaries.

677
00:45:11,083 --> 00:45:13,165
Huh. They're his gnomes, aren't they?

678
00:45:13,166 --> 00:45:15,665
I'm just... I'm getting the feeling that...

679
00:45:15,666 --> 00:45:17,832
Well, he may not be our man.

680
00:45:17,833 --> 00:45:21,541
[Mackintosh] That Wallace is a wrong 'un.
End of story.

681
00:45:25,500 --> 00:45:28,875
[Mackintosh] Now, if you don't mind,
we'll deal with that villain later.

682
00:45:29,458 --> 00:45:33,374
Right now, we've got important duties
to attend to up at the museum.

683
00:45:33,375 --> 00:45:34,291
But, sir...

684
00:45:34,875 --> 00:45:36,624
It's my big day, Mukherjee.

685
00:45:36,625 --> 00:45:40,082
The culmination of 40 years of service.

686
00:45:40,083 --> 00:45:43,165
- Nothing can go wrong.
- [Mukherjee] Er, no, sir.

687
00:45:43,166 --> 00:45:45,125
We have to stay focused.

688
00:45:45,958 --> 00:45:47,665
Watch like hawks.

689
00:45:47,666 --> 00:45:48,958
Absolutely, sir.

690
00:45:50,000 --> 00:45:51,208
Miss nothing.

691
00:45:52,166 --> 00:45:53,165
- [thuds]
- [Mukherjee] Huh?

692
00:45:53,166 --> 00:45:55,082
- [Mackintosh] Eh?
- Hmm.

693
00:45:55,083 --> 00:45:56,165
[Mackintosh sighs]

694
00:45:56,166 --> 00:45:58,250
[radar beeping]

695
00:46:32,541 --> 00:46:34,457
- [brakes squealing]
- [car horn blaring]

696
00:46:34,458 --> 00:46:36,166
[tyres screeching]

697
00:46:43,583 --> 00:46:45,583
[radar continues beeping]

698
00:46:52,125 --> 00:46:54,125
[suspenseful score playing]

699
00:47:06,458 --> 00:47:08,458
[soft rumbling]

700
00:47:16,833 --> 00:47:18,833
[rumbling continues]

701
00:47:24,625 --> 00:47:26,625
[bubbling softly]

702
00:47:48,500 --> 00:47:51,499
- [animals growling]
- [elephant trumpets]

703
00:47:51,500 --> 00:47:53,291
[animals calling]

704
00:48:08,291 --> 00:48:10,291
[dramatic sting plays]

705
00:48:11,000 --> 00:48:13,000
[baby seal purring]

706
00:48:19,000 --> 00:48:21,000
[water bubbling]

707
00:48:25,916 --> 00:48:26,916
[toy squeaks]

708
00:48:30,666 --> 00:48:32,666
[ominous score playing]

709
00:49:01,083 --> 00:49:02,458
[baby seal purrs]

710
00:49:06,375 --> 00:49:08,375
[bagpipes playing ceremonial music]

711
00:49:22,541 --> 00:49:23,624
- [screams]
- [music stops]

712
00:49:23,625 --> 00:49:24,708
[water splashes]

713
00:49:49,291 --> 00:49:50,416
[sawing]

714
00:49:51,750 --> 00:49:52,750
[branch creaks]

715
00:49:57,416 --> 00:49:58,333
[yelps]

716
00:49:59,500 --> 00:50:00,500
Ah.

717
00:50:03,291 --> 00:50:04,416
[chimes]

718
00:50:06,250 --> 00:50:08,915
- Reset mode activated.
- [computerised trilling]

719
00:50:08,916 --> 00:50:10,000
[gurgling]

720
00:50:11,125 --> 00:50:13,125
[bubbling, splashing nearby]

721
00:50:22,833 --> 00:50:24,833
[low growling]

722
00:50:26,666 --> 00:50:28,666
[dramatic score playing]

723
00:50:30,666 --> 00:50:31,875
[roars]

724
00:50:39,666 --> 00:50:40,666
Hmm?

725
00:50:41,583 --> 00:50:42,583
[grunting]

726
00:50:43,833 --> 00:50:44,999
Huh?

727
00:50:45,000 --> 00:50:47,083
[trilling, gurgling]

728
00:50:56,041 --> 00:50:58,625
Restored to inventor settings.

729
00:50:59,291 --> 00:51:02,375
Hi, I'm your Nifty Odd-jobbing Robot.

730
00:51:02,958 --> 00:51:04,375
Call me Norbot.

731
00:51:10,416 --> 00:51:12,415
Initiating pruning process.

732
00:51:12,416 --> 00:51:13,749
[rapid snipping]

733
00:51:13,750 --> 00:51:15,458
Neat and tidy.

734
00:51:16,458 --> 00:51:17,665
[roars]

735
00:51:17,666 --> 00:51:19,291
Huh? Hmm.

736
00:51:21,208 --> 00:51:24,208
[Bach's "Toccata and Fugue in D Minor"
playing on organ]

737
00:51:43,458 --> 00:51:44,458
[slurping]

738
00:51:45,583 --> 00:51:48,582
- [Evil Norbot 1] Set coordinates.
- [Evil Norbot 2] Target located.

739
00:51:48,583 --> 00:51:50,166
Two degrees West. Tracking.

740
00:51:52,916 --> 00:51:53,916
[beeping]

741
00:52:00,458 --> 00:52:02,333
No job is too small.

742
00:52:05,125 --> 00:52:06,625
Neat and tidy!

743
00:52:08,208 --> 00:52:09,582
[Norbot whoops]

744
00:52:09,583 --> 00:52:11,999
[Mackintosh] Right. Here we go, then.

745
00:52:12,000 --> 00:52:13,750
This is it, Mukherjee.

746
00:52:14,666 --> 00:52:15,499
Are we ready?

747
00:52:15,500 --> 00:52:17,375
Couldn't be readier, Chief.

748
00:52:32,750 --> 00:52:35,124
[Norbot] <i>♪ I'm a happy, nifty Norbot ♪</i>

749
00:52:35,125 --> 00:52:36,708
<i>♪ I love to do a job ♪</i>

750
00:52:37,791 --> 00:52:42,999
[Mackintosh] <i>It's been my great pride,
over the years, to serve this community.</i>

751
00:52:43,000 --> 00:52:45,082
Knowing there's nothing more reassuring

752
00:52:45,083 --> 00:52:47,749
than the sight
of an uninformed police officer.

753
00:52:47,750 --> 00:52:48,665
[guests gasp]

754
00:52:48,666 --> 00:52:49,750
[clears throat]

755
00:52:50,333 --> 00:52:51,333
Sorry.

756
00:52:52,000 --> 00:52:55,624
Oh! "Uniformed!" <i>Uniformed</i> police officer.

757
00:52:55,625 --> 00:52:57,499
Can't read me own writing.

758
00:52:57,500 --> 00:53:03,166
Anyway, now I have
one final happy duty to perform.

759
00:53:05,666 --> 00:53:07,583
Contact imminent.

760
00:53:16,916 --> 00:53:18,000
Going up.

761
00:53:23,291 --> 00:53:24,375
[Norbot] Coming through!

762
00:53:25,583 --> 00:53:26,583
[warbling]

763
00:53:33,291 --> 00:53:36,375
Ladies and gentlemen, shall we?

764
00:53:56,166 --> 00:53:58,749
[Mackintosh] And there we have it,
ladies and gentlemen.

765
00:53:58,750 --> 00:54:01,458
Safely on display for all posterity.

766
00:54:02,041 --> 00:54:04,541
- The Blue Diamond!
- [cameras clicking]

767
00:54:06,166 --> 00:54:07,333
[gasps]

768
00:54:09,583 --> 00:54:12,083
It's not as shiny in real life, is it?

769
00:54:12,666 --> 00:54:13,832
You what?

770
00:54:13,833 --> 00:54:15,582
[cameras clicking]

771
00:54:15,583 --> 00:54:16,916
What...

772
00:54:17,458 --> 00:54:19,790
That's a flippin' turnip!

773
00:54:19,791 --> 00:54:20,957
[all gasp]

774
00:54:20,958 --> 00:54:25,457
You didn't check inside the sack, Chief,
before you put it in the vault?

775
00:54:25,458 --> 00:54:26,583
Er...

776
00:54:27,458 --> 00:54:28,541
Oh...

777
00:54:33,750 --> 00:54:36,250
Right. Anyone fancy a pint?

778
00:54:37,208 --> 00:54:38,958
- Oh.
- [guests murmuring]

779
00:54:39,583 --> 00:54:43,666
So, if you've been guarding a turnip
all these years,

780
00:54:44,541 --> 00:54:47,583
then where is the Blue Diamond?

781
00:54:52,125 --> 00:54:53,125
[radar beeping]

782
00:54:59,458 --> 00:55:01,082
[plays discordant notes, sighs]

783
00:55:01,083 --> 00:55:02,583
Gnomes have gone.

784
00:55:03,125 --> 00:55:04,666
Gadgets have gone.

785
00:55:06,875 --> 00:55:08,665
Even me dog's gone.

786
00:55:08,666 --> 00:55:10,374
- [rumbling]
- Huh?

787
00:55:10,375 --> 00:55:11,875
What on earth?

788
00:55:14,083 --> 00:55:14,916
[gasps]

789
00:55:18,708 --> 00:55:21,250
I didn't know it could do that.

790
00:55:23,083 --> 00:55:25,375
What the dickens?

791
00:55:36,541 --> 00:55:37,541
[door creaking open]

792
00:55:38,625 --> 00:55:41,415
[Wallace] Come in, Gromit.
Everything's fine.

793
00:55:41,416 --> 00:55:43,083
Just come straight in.

794
00:55:47,666 --> 00:55:49,500
[muffled speech]

795
00:55:51,333 --> 00:55:54,125
[in Wallace's voice] Everything's fine.
Just come straight in.

796
00:55:54,791 --> 00:55:56,790
[in normal voice] Everything's fine.

797
00:55:56,791 --> 00:55:57,874
Everything's fine.

798
00:55:57,875 --> 00:56:01,291
- Everything's fine.
- Everything's fine.

799
00:56:03,333 --> 00:56:04,958
This is a disaster!

800
00:56:05,750 --> 00:56:08,332
This has made me
the laughing stock of the town.

801
00:56:08,333 --> 00:56:10,624
Er, sir, are you okay?

802
00:56:10,625 --> 00:56:13,749
[clears throat] I'm fine.
Just got an allergy to turnips.

803
00:56:13,750 --> 00:56:16,082
Should we haul Feathers in, sir?

804
00:56:16,083 --> 00:56:17,625
He had the diamond last.

805
00:56:18,708 --> 00:56:19,583
No.

806
00:56:20,666 --> 00:56:21,874
No, he didn't.

807
00:56:21,875 --> 00:56:24,415
What? You mean...

808
00:56:24,416 --> 00:56:26,500
Exactly. Come on.

809
00:56:27,166 --> 00:56:29,165
[foreboding score playing]

810
00:56:29,166 --> 00:56:30,458
[owl hoots]

811
00:56:34,333 --> 00:56:35,333
[Wallace grunting]

812
00:56:39,166 --> 00:56:41,540
[panting] I'm sorry
I couldn't warn you, lad.

813
00:56:41,541 --> 00:56:43,582
I got grabbed by the Norbots.

814
00:56:43,583 --> 00:56:46,083
A very unpleasant experience.

815
00:56:46,916 --> 00:56:48,915
Turns out they are bad, after all.

816
00:56:48,916 --> 00:56:50,749
I just don't get it.

817
00:56:50,750 --> 00:56:53,916
Why would me own gnomes turn against me?

818
00:57:01,000 --> 00:57:04,083
A chicken? Behind all this?

819
00:57:07,291 --> 00:57:09,458
Good grief! It's you!

820
00:57:10,333 --> 00:57:11,333
Again!

821
00:57:13,750 --> 00:57:16,000
But you're supposed to be locked up.

822
00:57:17,125 --> 00:57:19,749
Well, you won't get away with it,
you know.

823
00:57:19,750 --> 00:57:22,250
Whatever it is
you're trying to get away with.

824
00:57:24,750 --> 00:57:25,750
Eh?

825
00:57:28,500 --> 00:57:30,125
[Wallace mumbles in confusion]

826
00:57:32,083 --> 00:57:34,499
Oh! Fancy a cup of tea, do you?

827
00:57:34,500 --> 00:57:36,041
[scoffs] The cheek of it!

828
00:57:37,000 --> 00:57:40,166
Well, I wouldn't bother with that teapot.
It doesn't work.

829
00:57:43,166 --> 00:57:44,166
Eh?

830
00:57:45,500 --> 00:57:47,999
- [dramatic sting playing]
- [teapot shatters]

831
00:57:48,000 --> 00:57:49,875
- [magical tinkling]
- What?

832
00:57:58,625 --> 00:58:01,791
Well, butter me crumpets! It can't be!

833
00:58:03,166 --> 00:58:05,083
It's the Blue Diamond.

834
00:58:05,708 --> 00:58:08,541
He must've switched it all that time ago.

835
00:58:09,125 --> 00:58:11,124
Oh, is that the police?

836
00:58:11,125 --> 00:58:14,833
We've got someone here
you might be interested in.

837
00:58:17,583 --> 00:58:19,208
He's a slippery one.

838
00:58:24,333 --> 00:58:26,540
Oh, so <i>that's</i> your plan.

839
00:58:26,541 --> 00:58:29,249
You get away scot-free with the diamond,

840
00:58:29,250 --> 00:58:32,916
and everyone thinks
I'm the evil inventor who stole it.

841
00:58:34,666 --> 00:58:35,957
Why, that's...

842
00:58:35,958 --> 00:58:37,833
That's... vengeance...

843
00:58:38,625 --> 00:58:40,250
most foul!

844
00:58:42,333 --> 00:58:44,125
- [door closes, lock clicks]
- Huh?

845
00:58:45,291 --> 00:58:46,416
[muffled] Oi, let us out!

846
00:58:47,291 --> 00:58:49,916
- [engine stalling]
- [mimicking engine revving]

847
00:58:52,875 --> 00:58:54,958
[mimicking engine accelerating]

848
00:58:55,958 --> 00:58:57,582
[mimicking tyres screeching]

849
00:58:57,583 --> 00:58:59,499
[mimicking engine revving]

850
00:58:59,500 --> 00:59:02,124
I can't believe
someone's nicked me bike saddle!

851
00:59:02,125 --> 00:59:03,582
[panting] I know, sir.

852
00:59:03,583 --> 00:59:05,915
Sorry, sir. You took me off that case.

853
00:59:05,916 --> 00:59:08,207
Still, we've got our culprit.

854
00:59:08,208 --> 00:59:09,957
[chuckles] All this time,

855
00:59:09,958 --> 00:59:12,166
Wallace just wanted the diamond
for himself.

856
00:59:12,875 --> 00:59:15,166
So, you were right all along, Chief.

857
00:59:15,791 --> 00:59:18,415
- [sighs] He is a wrong 'un.
- Aye, too right.

858
00:59:18,416 --> 00:59:21,833
And if he thinks he's got away with this,
he's got another thing coming.

859
00:59:23,208 --> 00:59:25,416
Oh, this is all my fault, lad.

860
00:59:26,333 --> 00:59:31,083
I only ever meant to invent good things,
things that help people.

861
00:59:31,458 --> 00:59:35,290
I never imagined
they could be used for wrongdoing.

862
00:59:35,291 --> 00:59:37,708
- [front door opens]
- [footsteps approaching]

863
00:59:38,833 --> 00:59:41,332
- Oh, heck, it's the law.
- [door unlocks]

864
00:59:41,333 --> 00:59:43,416
- I'm done for now.
- [door creaking open]

865
00:59:45,833 --> 00:59:48,541
Morning, Mr Wallace. Master Gromit.

866
00:59:49,125 --> 00:59:51,499
Norbot! Where have you been?

867
00:59:51,500 --> 00:59:53,583
No job is too small.

868
00:59:54,166 --> 00:59:57,582
Sounds like
he's back to his nifty odd-jobbing self.

869
00:59:57,583 --> 01:00:00,333
We're saved! [laughs]

870
01:00:00,916 --> 01:00:02,832
[Norbot] Neat and tidy!

871
01:00:02,833 --> 01:00:04,207
- [door closes]
- Huh?

872
01:00:04,208 --> 01:00:07,665
- [lock clicks]
- Wait, Norbot! Come back!

873
01:00:07,666 --> 01:00:09,540
- [vacuum cleaner whirring]
- Don't worry, lad.

874
01:00:09,541 --> 01:00:12,374
He's voice-activated. Hmm. Norbot!

875
01:00:12,375 --> 01:00:13,707
<i>♪ I'm a happy, nifty Norbot ♪</i>

876
01:00:13,708 --> 01:00:14,790
[Wallace muffled] Norbot!

877
01:00:14,791 --> 01:00:16,082
<i>♪ I love to clean the house ♪</i>

878
01:00:16,083 --> 01:00:18,166
Norbot! Norbot!

879
01:00:20,583 --> 01:00:23,208
Norbot! Norbot!

880
01:00:27,500 --> 01:00:28,750
Steady on!

881
01:00:29,375 --> 01:00:30,375
Huh?

882
01:00:31,083 --> 01:00:32,458
What are you up to, lad?

883
01:00:34,875 --> 01:00:35,874
[whirring]

884
01:00:35,875 --> 01:00:38,749
Hardly the time to start leaf-blowing!

885
01:00:38,750 --> 01:00:41,250
What on earth! [screaming]

886
01:00:42,875 --> 01:00:43,875
[Norbot whooping]

887
01:00:44,458 --> 01:00:46,124
[shouting] Gromit!

888
01:00:46,125 --> 01:00:47,583
[Norbot] Collision warning!

889
01:00:49,208 --> 01:00:52,333
Right. Someone's got
a big surprise coming.

890
01:00:53,333 --> 01:00:55,750
- [Wallace] Sorry!
- Chief, they're getting away!

891
01:00:56,791 --> 01:00:59,208
- Chief?
- [doorbell rings]

892
01:01:01,541 --> 01:01:02,750
Did we get him?

893
01:01:04,375 --> 01:01:07,500
<i>♪ Born free ♪</i>

894
01:01:08,083 --> 01:01:12,333
<i>♪ As free as the wind blows ♪</i>

895
01:01:13,083 --> 01:01:16,958
<i>- ♪ As free as the grass grows ♪</i>
- [Evil Norbots heaving]

896
01:01:19,583 --> 01:01:20,833
[Wallace] Careful!

897
01:01:22,208 --> 01:01:23,415
There's Feathers!

898
01:01:23,416 --> 01:01:24,999
Nice work, Gromit!

899
01:01:25,000 --> 01:01:27,082
Let's get after the bounder.

900
01:01:27,083 --> 01:01:28,540
More speed, Mr Wallace?

901
01:01:28,541 --> 01:01:29,541
[Wallace] Eh?

902
01:01:30,375 --> 01:01:31,708
Whoa!

903
01:01:32,416 --> 01:01:35,041
Steady, Norbot. Take her up, Gromit.

904
01:01:36,833 --> 01:01:39,791
Hand over the diamond, you little tyke!

905
01:01:40,916 --> 01:01:43,333
- Norbot, fetch.
- Righto.

906
01:01:44,166 --> 01:01:46,749
[Wallace] That's it. That's it, Norbot.

907
01:01:46,750 --> 01:01:48,250
- [tyres screech]
- [gasps]

908
01:01:50,333 --> 01:01:52,082
[Evil Norbot] Banana alert!

909
01:01:52,083 --> 01:01:53,333
Skidding!

910
01:01:53,916 --> 01:01:55,624
[Wallace screaming]

911
01:01:55,625 --> 01:01:56,625
[all screaming]

912
01:01:59,958 --> 01:02:01,040
[crashing]

913
01:02:01,041 --> 01:02:02,625
[Evil Norbots] Ow! Ow! Ouch!

914
01:02:04,041 --> 01:02:05,790
[Wallace] There he is! After him!

915
01:02:05,791 --> 01:02:07,166
[screaming]

916
01:02:16,791 --> 01:02:19,416
Norbot, stop this thing!

917
01:02:20,083 --> 01:02:21,291
Yes, Mr Wallace.

918
01:02:22,833 --> 01:02:24,916
[Wallace] Not like that!

919
01:02:25,791 --> 01:02:27,665
Whoa!

920
01:02:27,666 --> 01:02:29,082
[thudding]

921
01:02:29,083 --> 01:02:31,582
Emergency stop complete.

922
01:02:31,583 --> 01:02:33,083
[Wallace groaning]

923
01:02:49,083 --> 01:02:50,541
[engine starting]

924
01:02:58,666 --> 01:02:59,916
Gromit?

925
01:03:00,333 --> 01:03:01,166
Whoa!

926
01:03:10,541 --> 01:03:12,749
- [engines chugging softly]
- [birds chirping]

927
01:03:12,750 --> 01:03:13,833
[dog sniffing]

928
01:03:14,666 --> 01:03:16,666
[woman humming softly]

929
01:03:21,708 --> 01:03:22,791
[laughs]

930
01:03:23,750 --> 01:03:25,832
[gasps] There they are, Chief!

931
01:03:25,833 --> 01:03:29,166
Oh, nice-looking narrowboat, that.
A bit like mine.

932
01:03:30,833 --> 01:03:31,833
Hang on a sec.

933
01:03:32,416 --> 01:03:33,624
That <i>is</i> mine!

934
01:03:33,625 --> 01:03:35,375
Hey! Stop in the name of the law!

935
01:03:38,250 --> 01:03:39,250
[grunting, laughing]

936
01:03:46,916 --> 01:03:49,707
[grunts] It's no use, lad.

937
01:03:49,708 --> 01:03:53,083
If only there were some way
of rebooting them.

938
01:03:57,708 --> 01:03:59,332
[groaning]

939
01:03:59,333 --> 01:04:01,624
<i>♪ I'm a happy, nifty Norbot ♪</i>

940
01:04:01,625 --> 01:04:03,915
<i>♪ I like to clean the boat ♪</i>

941
01:04:03,916 --> 01:04:04,833
Ah!

942
01:04:08,541 --> 01:04:09,541
[grunts]

943
01:04:12,000 --> 01:04:13,000
Huh?

944
01:04:16,208 --> 01:04:17,625
Another invention?

945
01:04:19,958 --> 01:04:21,250
Are you sure, lad?

946
01:04:26,750 --> 01:04:30,750
Right, then.
Technical assistance is on its way.

947
01:04:31,416 --> 01:04:33,415
Can't believe he nicked me boat.

948
01:04:33,416 --> 01:04:35,083
And you thought he was innocent!

949
01:04:38,416 --> 01:04:40,040
{\an8}[Mukherjee gasps] I think...

950
01:04:40,041 --> 01:04:42,749
I think that's Feathers McGraw, Chief.

951
01:04:42,750 --> 01:04:44,165
They're trying to stop...

952
01:04:44,166 --> 01:04:46,415
- [over megaphone] ...Feathers McGraw!
- Feathers McGraw?

953
01:04:46,416 --> 01:04:48,124
Don't be ridiculous!

954
01:04:48,125 --> 01:04:50,000
He's banged up in the zoo!

955
01:04:52,916 --> 01:04:56,124
That's just an innocent nun
out for a pleasure cruise.

956
01:04:56,125 --> 01:05:01,124
I just think maybe Wallace has been
unfairly portrayed as a crazed inventor...

957
01:05:01,125 --> 01:05:02,624
- [door opens]
- [both gasp]

958
01:05:02,625 --> 01:05:05,457
[laughing manically]

959
01:05:05,458 --> 01:05:07,332
Oh, this'll work a treat!

960
01:05:07,333 --> 01:05:10,249
- [Mackintosh] Huh?
- ...to a certain extent.

961
01:05:10,250 --> 01:05:11,165
What the...

962
01:05:11,166 --> 01:05:13,833
What's he done
with me vintage boot collection?

963
01:05:17,000 --> 01:05:22,750
Okay, Gromit. Let's give those gnomes
a good reboot up the backside!

964
01:05:28,750 --> 01:05:30,666
- [cackling]
- Missed!

965
01:05:35,208 --> 01:05:38,375
- [Wallace] Bullseye!
- Reset mode activated.

966
01:05:39,541 --> 01:05:41,207
[Wallace] It's working, lad!

967
01:05:41,208 --> 01:05:43,208
[laughs] Give it more welly!

968
01:05:45,541 --> 01:05:46,833
Take that!

969
01:05:48,416 --> 01:05:49,665
Hoodlums!

970
01:05:49,666 --> 01:05:51,583
[Evil Norbot] Reset mode activated.

971
01:05:53,500 --> 01:05:55,500
Reset mode activated.

972
01:05:56,000 --> 01:05:57,915
This has gone far enough.

973
01:05:57,916 --> 01:05:59,207
Chief Inspector Mac,

974
01:05:59,208 --> 01:06:02,999
all units pursue
and arrest Wallace... [grunts]

975
01:06:03,000 --> 01:06:05,666
Sorry, Chief, I'm using me gut.

976
01:06:06,166 --> 01:06:08,374
Calling all units! Head to the border.

977
01:06:08,375 --> 01:06:10,374
Suspect is <i>not</i> Wallace,

978
01:06:10,375 --> 01:06:13,249
but a small nun in charge of a canal boat.

979
01:06:13,250 --> 01:06:15,332
You're in big trouble, Mukherjee!

980
01:06:15,333 --> 01:06:18,207
Yeah! This is going on
your assessment report, this!

981
01:06:18,208 --> 01:06:21,499
[burbling] Reset mode activated.

982
01:06:21,500 --> 01:06:22,583
[chiming]

983
01:06:23,916 --> 01:06:26,957
[Norbots] Hi.
I'm your Nifty Odd-jobbing Robot.

984
01:06:26,958 --> 01:06:27,874
Call me Norbot.

985
01:06:27,875 --> 01:06:29,707
- [overlapping chatter]
- Pleased to meet you.

986
01:06:29,708 --> 01:06:30,624
[warbles]

987
01:06:30,625 --> 01:06:32,540
Caught a few tiddlers, have you?

988
01:06:32,541 --> 01:06:33,832
Good lad.

989
01:06:33,833 --> 01:06:35,582
Now we've got him.

990
01:06:35,583 --> 01:06:38,207
Eh? Where's he gone?

991
01:06:38,208 --> 01:06:39,958
[engine revving in distance]

992
01:06:45,291 --> 01:06:46,166
Huh?

993
01:06:56,333 --> 01:06:57,832
[Wallace] Well done, lad.

994
01:06:57,833 --> 01:07:00,458
We've got him! [yelling]

995
01:07:07,791 --> 01:07:10,374
Grom... it!

996
01:07:10,375 --> 01:07:13,083
Don't let him get away! [screaming]

997
01:07:15,708 --> 01:07:18,208
Whoa! [whimpering]

998
01:07:38,708 --> 01:07:39,708
[yelping]

999
01:07:43,000 --> 01:07:44,958
- [grunts] Sorry!
- Huh?

1000
01:07:46,500 --> 01:07:47,333
[squeals]

1001
01:07:59,625 --> 01:08:02,082
[Wallace yelping] Oh, Gromit!

1002
01:08:02,083 --> 01:08:03,790
[grunting] Huh?

1003
01:08:03,791 --> 01:08:05,000
[screams]

1004
01:08:06,375 --> 01:08:07,583
Oh, lummy!

1005
01:08:09,166 --> 01:08:10,041
Huh?

1006
01:08:10,833 --> 01:08:11,665
Why, ya...

1007
01:08:11,666 --> 01:08:14,083
[dramatic angelic score playing]

1008
01:08:30,041 --> 01:08:32,000
[Wallace screaming]

1009
01:08:35,333 --> 01:08:36,166
Ouch!

1010
01:08:47,291 --> 01:08:48,666
[sirens wailing]

1011
01:08:51,708 --> 01:08:54,166
[gasps] I knew it was Feathers McGraw!

1012
01:08:55,541 --> 01:08:57,000
Quick, close the gate.

1013
01:09:27,125 --> 01:09:28,875
[gasps] Gromit!

1014
01:09:35,125 --> 01:09:36,625
[whimpering]

1015
01:09:42,875 --> 01:09:44,875
[boat creaking]

1016
01:10:01,666 --> 01:10:03,833
Give him the diamond, lad.

1017
01:10:04,541 --> 01:10:07,165
I can live without inventing,

1018
01:10:07,166 --> 01:10:10,208
but I can't live without... [gulps]

1019
01:10:13,000 --> 01:10:14,750
...me best pal.

1020
01:10:17,291 --> 01:10:19,666
[dramatic score playing]

1021
01:10:32,083 --> 01:10:33,083
[score stops]

1022
01:10:36,000 --> 01:10:38,000
[boat creaking]

1023
01:10:43,916 --> 01:10:44,750
[gasps softly]

1024
01:10:46,666 --> 01:10:48,666
- [train chugging below]
- [horn blaring]

1025
01:11:02,625 --> 01:11:03,625
[boat creaking]

1026
01:11:07,625 --> 01:11:08,500
No!

1027
01:11:13,625 --> 01:11:19,083
[in slow motion] Gromit!

1028
01:11:21,166 --> 01:11:25,958
No!

1029
01:11:40,083 --> 01:11:43,290
Hi. I'm your Nifty Odd-jobbing Robot.

1030
01:11:43,291 --> 01:11:45,000
Call me Norbot.

1031
01:11:46,000 --> 01:11:47,166
[Norbots] How may I help you?

1032
01:11:56,333 --> 01:11:58,541
No job is too small.

1033
01:12:00,333 --> 01:12:01,332
[Norbots] Aww!

1034
01:12:01,333 --> 01:12:05,458
I knew you would embrace technology
in the end, lad.

1035
01:12:06,916 --> 01:12:09,250
Thank goodness you're safe.

1036
01:12:10,416 --> 01:12:12,540
All right! Break it up!

1037
01:12:12,541 --> 01:12:14,165
This is a crime scene now.

1038
01:12:14,166 --> 01:12:15,874
Chief! Chief!

1039
01:12:15,875 --> 01:12:19,165
I haven't got time
for your apologies, Mukherjee.

1040
01:12:19,166 --> 01:12:21,500
- [exasperated sigh]
- Just arrest Wallace for...

1041
01:12:23,416 --> 01:12:24,791
Flippin' nora!

1042
01:12:25,750 --> 01:12:27,625
It <i>is</i> Feathers McGraw!

1043
01:12:30,708 --> 01:12:32,583
And he's got the diamond.

1044
01:12:33,166 --> 01:12:36,083
Oh, that's ruined me retirement, that has.

1045
01:12:48,250 --> 01:12:49,457
Wait? What?

1046
01:12:49,458 --> 01:12:51,374
[both laugh]

1047
01:12:51,375 --> 01:12:53,665
The old turnip switcheroo!

1048
01:12:53,666 --> 01:12:55,832
Oh, cracking move, lad!

1049
01:12:55,833 --> 01:12:58,165
- [Norbots cheer]
- [Norbot] Cracking move, lad!

1050
01:12:58,166 --> 01:12:59,708
[Norbots] Bravo!

1051
01:13:00,791 --> 01:13:02,958
[Wallace] Ha! That told him, Gromit.

1052
01:13:03,875 --> 01:13:05,790
He's a bad egg, that one.

1053
01:13:05,791 --> 01:13:07,958
And a scoundrel to boot.

1054
01:13:14,833 --> 01:13:17,833
I think you should have this, Officer.

1055
01:13:18,791 --> 01:13:22,040
Well, considering what I've just seen,

1056
01:13:22,041 --> 01:13:25,415
it looks like Mukherjee was right
about you being innocent.

1057
01:13:25,416 --> 01:13:26,500
You mean,

1058
01:13:27,166 --> 01:13:28,957
I'm not going to jail?

1059
01:13:28,958 --> 01:13:32,875
No. Thanks to the instincts
of a fine young copper.

1060
01:13:33,458 --> 01:13:35,457
You're a natural, Mukherjee.

1061
01:13:35,458 --> 01:13:38,666
Oh, thanks, Chief. That means a lot.

1062
01:13:39,458 --> 01:13:41,707
- Happy retirement, sir.
- [Wallace chuckles]

1063
01:13:41,708 --> 01:13:45,790
Well, this is a <i>turnip</i> for the books,
eh, lad?

1064
01:13:45,791 --> 01:13:47,040
Hmm.

1065
01:13:47,041 --> 01:13:48,499
[Norbots laughing]

1066
01:13:48,500 --> 01:13:51,582
[Norbot] Oh, yes! Very funny, Mr Wallace!

1067
01:13:51,583 --> 01:13:53,666
[whimsical score playing]

1068
01:14:03,375 --> 01:14:04,375
[sighs]

1069
01:14:05,458 --> 01:14:06,458
Oh.

1070
01:14:07,666 --> 01:14:08,875
Hmm. [chuckles]

1071
01:14:11,666 --> 01:14:12,750
[sighs]

1072
01:14:17,875 --> 01:14:19,375
[Mackintosh sighs] Ah, yes.

1073
01:14:22,416 --> 01:14:23,791
{\an8}[sighs]

1074
01:14:25,791 --> 01:14:27,999
Oh, hey! Hey, What's this? What...

1075
01:14:28,000 --> 01:14:30,665
- [indistinct music on headphones]
- Can't you read, sonny Jim?

1076
01:14:30,666 --> 01:14:33,624
{\an8}- Maximum speed four miles per hour.
- [siren wailing]

1077
01:14:33,625 --> 01:14:37,000
{\an8}That's three points on your licence
for a start!

1078
01:14:41,708 --> 01:14:43,290
[Wallace] Morning, Gromit.

1079
01:14:43,291 --> 01:14:46,041
How's my favourite pooch, hmm?

1080
01:14:48,375 --> 01:14:51,665
Oh, I've got something
for your garden, lad.

1081
01:14:51,666 --> 01:14:54,124
[dramatic sting plays]

1082
01:14:54,125 --> 01:14:56,833
I've repurposed the Pat-O-Matic.

1083
01:15:00,333 --> 01:15:05,666
After all, necessity is
the mother-in-law of invention. [chuckles]

1084
01:15:14,416 --> 01:15:15,541
Da-na!

1085
01:15:16,125 --> 01:15:17,207
[Wallace] Aww.

1086
01:15:17,208 --> 01:15:22,500
Oh, but there's some things
a machine just can't do, eh, lad?

1087
01:15:23,083 --> 01:15:27,624
Aww! Aww! [chuckles] Aww!

1088
01:15:27,625 --> 01:15:30,083
Aww, yes. [chuckles]

1089
01:15:31,583 --> 01:15:33,291
Cheers, me old pal.

1090
01:15:34,875 --> 01:15:37,290
[Norbot] <i>♪ I'm a happy, nifty Norbot ♪</i>

1091
01:15:37,291 --> 01:15:39,125
<i>♪ I like to trim the hedge ♪</i>

1092
01:15:42,208 --> 01:15:43,707
Da-na!

1093
01:15:43,708 --> 01:15:45,791
[whimsical score playing]

1094
01:17:14,333 --> 01:17:17,624
[Norbots] <i>♪ We're happy, nifty Norbots
We love to do our job ♪</i>

1095
01:17:17,625 --> 01:17:20,957
<i>♪ When we come round and fix your house
We make up quite a mob ♪</i>

1096
01:17:20,958 --> 01:17:24,374
<i>♪ We dig and paint, we plant and snip
We'll break our little backs ♪</i>

1097
01:17:24,375 --> 01:17:28,040
<i>♪ And never stop to have a brew
'Cause we got battery packs ♪</i>

1098
01:17:28,041 --> 01:17:30,125
[score continues]

